The paper discusses high performance computing workloads in the exascale era, which is a topic that falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also proposes multiscale computing patterns as a way to achieve load balancing, fault tolerance, and energy efficiency, which could fall under the Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS) sub-category. The paper also discusses the separation of concerns between application developers and pattern software, which could fall under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the extreme scaling pattern, which could fall under the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses energy-aware computing, which could fall under the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
